[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":351},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F17\u002Fmac-port-already-in-use-fix\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F17\u002Fmac-port-already-in-use-fix\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F17\u002Fmac-port-already-in-use-fix\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F17\u002Fmac-port-already-in-use-fix\u002F":326,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F17\u002Fmac-port-already-in-use-fix\u002F":335},"\u002Fother\u002F20220117\u002F241830554\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":306,"date":307,"description":308,"extension":309,"lang":310,"meta":311,"navigation":312,"path":313,"readingMinutes":314,"seo":315,"standalone":316,"stem":317,"tags":318,"tldr":322,"updated":323,"url":324,"__hash__":325},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Fmac-port-already-in-use-fix.md","Mac \"Port xxx is Already in Use\" — How to Free It Up","5418300251",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":295},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,32,38,54,57,66,73,76,107,116,127,136,142,145,156,160,167,170,174,181,190,193,199,206,212,218,222,228,234,237,242,245,251,254,260,266,270,273,276,282,285,291],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"When you're building something locally, you'll sometimes hit \"Port 5000 is already in use\" or similar. So I'm writing down how to clear a busy port.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"check-the-port","Check the port",[17,25,26,27,31],{},"When your server complains \"Port ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"xxxx"," is already in use\", open a terminal and check whether it's actually in use:",[17,33,34,35,37],{},"(Replace ",[28,36,30],{}," with the port number.)",[39,40,45],"pre",{"className":41,"code":42,"language":43,"meta":44,"style":44},"language-cmd shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","lsof -i:xxxx\n","cmd","",[28,46,47],{"__ignoreMap":44},[48,49,52],"span",{"class":50,"line":51},"line",1,[48,53,42],{},[17,55,56],{},"For port 5000:",[39,58,60],{"className":41,"code":59,"language":43,"meta":44,"style":44},"lsof -i:5000\n",[28,61,62],{"__ignoreMap":44},[48,63,64],{"class":50,"line":51},[48,65,59],{},[17,67,68],{},[69,70],"img",{"alt":71,"src":72},"lsof output","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-17%2014.03.09.png",[17,74,75],{},"The output has these columns:",[77,78,79,83,86,89,92,95,98,101,104],"ul",{},[80,81,82],"li",{},"COMMAND",[80,84,85],{},"PID",[80,87,88],{},"USER",[80,90,91],{},"FD",[80,93,94],{},"TYPE",[80,96,97],{},"DEVICE",[80,99,100],{},"SIZE\u002FOFF",[80,102,103],{},"NODE",[80,105,106],{},"NAME",[17,108,109,110,112,113,115],{},"You only care about two — ",[28,111,82],{}," and ",[28,114,85],{},".",[17,117,118,119,122,123,126],{},"If permission errors block ",[28,120,121],{},"lsof -i:xxxx",", prepend ",[28,124,125],{},"sudo",":",[39,128,130],{"className":41,"code":129,"language":43,"meta":44,"style":44},"sudo lsof -i:5000\n",[28,131,132],{"__ignoreMap":44},[48,133,134],{"class":50,"line":51},[48,135,129],{},[17,137,138,139,141],{},"In the screenshot, ",[28,140,82],{}," shows it's Node holding the port — so check if you've got a forgotten Node window running somewhere.",[17,143,144],{},"If you want to see every port that's in use:",[39,146,150],{"className":147,"code":148,"language":149,"meta":44,"style":44},"language-node shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","lsof -n -i\n","node",[28,151,152],{"__ignoreMap":44},[48,153,154],{"class":50,"line":51},[48,155,148],{},[12,157,159],{"id":158},"stop-release-clear-the-port","Stop \u002F release \u002F clear the port",[17,161,162,163,166],{},"If you really can't track down the source, just ",[28,164,165],{},"kill PID"," to free the port.",[17,168,169],{},"Using the screenshot example:",[17,171,172],{},[69,173],{"alt":71,"src":72},[17,175,176,177,180],{},"PID is ",[28,178,179],{},"19625",", so:",[39,182,184],{"className":41,"code":183,"language":43,"meta":44,"style":44},"kill 19625\n",[28,185,186],{"__ignoreMap":44},[48,187,188],{"class":50,"line":51},[48,189,183],{},[17,191,192],{},"You won't get any output back:",[17,194,195],{},[69,196],{"alt":197,"src":198},"kill","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-17%2014.14.48.png",[17,200,201,202,205],{},"But re-run ",[28,203,204],{},"lsof -i:5000"," and the port should be free:",[17,207,208],{},[69,209],{"alt":210,"src":211},"lsof","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-17%2014.15.02.png",[17,213,214,215,115],{},"If you had a server terminal open, you might see it print something like ",[28,216,217],{},"[1] 19624 terminated  npm start",[12,219,221],{"id":220},"the-undead-5000-port-on-macos","The undead 5000 port on macOS",[17,223,224,225,227],{},"macOS has a special problem — port 5000 just gets eaten, and no matter how many times you ",[28,226,197],{}," it, the process pops right back up:",[17,229,230],{},[69,231],{"alt":232,"src":233},"Port 5000 keeps coming back","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-17%2014.30.50.png",[17,235,236],{},"Cause — something in macOS's Control Center is grabbing port 5000.",[238,239,241],"h3",{"id":240},"the-fix","The fix",[17,243,244],{},"Open \"System Preferences\" and search \"Sharing\":",[17,246,247],{},[69,248],{"alt":249,"src":250},"Sharing","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-01-17%2014.35.18.png",[17,252,253],{},"Inside Sharing, find \"AirPlay Receiver\" and uncheck it:",[17,255,256],{},[69,257],{"alt":258,"src":259},"AirPlay Receiver","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96_2022-01-17_14_40_22.png",[17,261,262,263,265],{},"Now ",[28,264,204],{}," should come back empty.",[238,267,269],{"id":268},"_2023-update-new-macos-ui","2023 update — new macOS UI",[17,271,272],{},"Apple redesigned System Settings in a newer macOS version, so the AirPlay Receiver toggle moved.",[17,274,275],{},"In the new System Settings, search \"AirPlay Receiver\" in the top search box:",[17,277,278],{},[69,279],{"alt":280,"src":281},"AirPlay Receiver search","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2010.13.55.png",[17,283,284],{},"Click into AirPlay Receiver, find the \"AirPlay Receiver\" toggle, and uncheck it:",[17,286,287],{},[69,288],{"alt":289,"src":290},"AirPlay Receiver toggle","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2010.15.47.png",[292,293,294],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":44,"searchDepth":296,"depth":296,"links":297},2,[298,299,300,301],{"id":14,"depth":296,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":296,"text":23},{"id":158,"depth":296,"text":159},{"id":220,"depth":296,"text":221,"children":302},[303,305],{"id":240,"depth":304,"text":241},3,{"id":268,"depth":304,"text":269},"Misc","2022-01-17 13:57:30","Building a project locally and hitting \"Port 5000 is already in use\"? This post covers how to identify what's holding a port on Mac (lsof), how to kill it (kill PID), and the special case of macOS reserving port 5000 for AirPlay Receiver — including the exact System Settings toggle to free it.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Fmac-port-already-in-use-fix","2",{"title":6,"description":308},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Fmac-port-already-in-use-fix",[319,320,321],"Port in Use","Mac","Troubleshooting",null,"2023-03-07 10:15:00","\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F17\u002Fmac-port-already-in-use-fix\u002F","zJAxxWamyFQibe2fbLuuhHQoPJ3VVio_HZ8fRaxt4yc",{"newer":327,"older":331},{"url":328,"title":329,"date":330},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F18\u002Fjavascript-multiple-left-hand-assignment\u002F","The JavaScript a = b = c Interview Question, Finally Explained","2022-01-18 09:09:39",{"url":332,"title":333,"date":334},"\u002Fen\u002Fnuxt\u002F2022\u002F01\u002F16\u002Fnuxt-2x-handbook-07-axios\u002F","Nuxt.js 2.x Hands-On Handbook (7) — Axios","2022-01-16 18:12:30",[336,341,346],{"url":337,"title":338,"date":339,"readingMinutes":340},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":342,"title":343,"date":344,"readingMinutes":345},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":347,"title":348,"date":349,"readingMinutes":350},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784010281705]